-- Fiat CEO flies to U.S. to discuss Chrysler: source
-- 
-- Thu May 28, 2009 5:48am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/05/28/us-gm-opel-fiat-sb-idUSTRE54R1YX20090528

 

 TURIN, Italy  (Reuters) - Fiat ( FIA.MI ) Chief Executive Sergio Marchionne is traveling to the United States to discuss issues concerning Chrysler LLC CBS.UL, a source at the Italian industrial group said on Thursday. 

 Marchionne leaves for the United States after taking part in overnight talks in Germany about the future of Opel, a unit of General Motors Corp ( GM.N ). Fiat is competing against Magna MGa.TO in a bidding war for Opel. Fiat has entered a partnership with Chrysler, which is going through bankruptcy court. (Reporting by Gianni Montani; writing by  Gilles Castonguay )